<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 5 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER ES70-5 - DISASSEMBLE - INPUT
        SHAFT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1301101" svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="2">
        <title>INPUT SHAFT</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The hole in the center allows lubricant to flow to the pocket bearing. Make sure it is free
                from contaminants and other obstructions (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301137">Figure 37</hotlnk>). Inspect the shaft and bearing cup for damage. Replace if
                necessary.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301137" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301137" filename="../figg13/G1301137.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 37. Lubricant Flow to Pocket Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Press the bearing off the shaft and replace it with a new one (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301138">Figure 38</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301138" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301138" filename="../figg13/G1301138.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 38. Replace With New Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Wear safety glasses to protect your eyes from flying metal pieces when pulling components off
                        or pressing them onto a shaft.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
